2:["$","article",null,{"className":"mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-muted","children":["2026-01-27"," · ","6 min read"]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-semibold","children":"Structuring Authentication in Hackathon Projects"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted","children":"How to ship secure auth quickly without sacrificing product velocity in short builds."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-neutral max-w-none leading-8","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":"Hackathons reward speed, but rushed authentication is one of the most common weak points in student projects. I used to treat auth as a late-stage feature, and every time, it created bugs and risky shortcuts. Now I build authentication as day-one infrastructure."}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Decide your threat model early"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"You do not need enterprise complexity in a 48-hour build, but you should still define likely risks:"}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"account takeover through weak passwords"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"token theft via browser storage"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"privilege escalation by missing route checks"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Writing these down early helps prioritize security controls."}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Favor secure defaults"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"My current baseline looks like this:"}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Passwords hashed with bcrypt or argon2"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Short-lived access token + refresh token rotation"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"HttpOnly cookies for session transport"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"CSRF protection on state-changing routes"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Role checks in middleware, not only in UI"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"These choices are small but prevent the most frequent failures."}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Keep auth boundaries clean"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"A frequent mistake is spreading auth logic across UI components. I now isolate it in three places:"}],"\n",["$","ol",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"API routes for sign-up/sign-in/session refresh"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"middleware for route access control"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"client hooks for session state"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"This separation improves both speed and correctness."}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Avoid hidden coupling"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"If your project has teams working in parallel, define auth contracts in plain language and types. For example:"}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"what claims exist in tokens"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"what roles can call each endpoint"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"what error format is returned"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Shared contracts prevent integration chaos near submission time."}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Add an audit trail"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Even in hackathon projects, basic event logging is useful. I record login attempts, refresh failures, and permission denials. These logs help diagnose issues quickly during demo day."}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Final note"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Good authentication is not about building the most complex stack. It is about reducing avoidable risk while preserving momentum. A minimal, structured auth layer creates confidence and saves time when pressure is highest."}]]}]]}]
